last_episode_to_air.overview: The Titans retreat to an underground bunker after a distress signal, where they enjoy footage from their past adventures, only to notice something isn't right.

name: Teen Titans Go!

next_episode_to_air.name: The Ranch
next_episode_to_air.overview: The Titans must accompany their animation team to the new offices.

overview: Robin, Starfire, Raven, Beast Boy and Cyborg return in all-new, comedic adventures. They may be super heroes who save the world every day ... but somebody still has to do the laundry!

episodes.name: Legendary Sandwich
episodes.overview: Beast Boy, Robin and Starfire go in search of the ingredients for a legendary sandwich.

episodes.name: Pie Bros
episodes.overview: Beast Boy gets a job at a pie shop in order to buy Cyborg a birthday gift.

episodes.name: Driver's Ed
episodes.overview: Robin takes driver's ed, and his teacher has some tricks up his sleeve.

episodes.name: Dog Hand
episodes.overview: Raven's dad cozies up to her friends in hopes of luring her over to the dark side.

episodes.name: Double Trouble
episodes.overview: Cyborg has Raven create doubles of himself and Beast Boy.

episodes.name: The Date
episodes.overview: To go on a date with Starfire, Robin kidnaps Speedy.

episodes.name: Dude Relax!
episodes.overview: The gang try to teach Robin to relax after his high-strung nature begins affecting the team. Later, chores pile up while the team bicker, and soon their dirty uniforms go on the offensive.

episodes.name: Laundry Day
episodes.overview: Later, chores pile up while the team bicker, and soon their dirty uniforms go on the offensive.

episodes.name: Ghostboy
episodes.overview: Beast Boy pretends to be a ghost haunting Starfire so she will do his bidding. When she figures out the ruse, she and the other Titans convince Beast Boy that he's actually dead.

episodes.name: La Larva de Amor
episodes.overview: Robin, Cyborg, Beast Boy, and Raven agree to take on the responsibility of babysitting Silkie while Starfire is away.

episodes.name: Hey Pizza!
episodes.overview: Cyborg and Beast Boy try to capitalize on Zippy's Pizza's "thirty minutes or its free" deal, but the delivery boy is seemingly unstoppable. It becomes a bit of a challenge as an all-out war of wits between them erupts. Meanwhile, Robin struggles with whether to build a senior center or a pool (leaning toward the pool mostly to see Starfire in a bikini).

episodes.name: Gorilla
episodes.overview: Beast Boy turns into a loud, obnoxious gorilla and refuses to change back driving Robin crazy. Gorilla Beast Boy takes over the leadership of the Titans leading to chaos ranging from not letting a girl get onto Beast Boy's monkey bars, fighting crocodiles, and freeing captive gorillas from the zoo. Cyborg teaches Robin how to be an alpha male so he can take back his role as leader of the Teen Titans.

episodes.name: Girl's Night Out
episodes.overview: When Robin, Cyborg, and Beast Boy won’t let Starfire and Raven come along on their "Boys' Night Out," Starfire and Raven spring Jinx from prison and the three of them have a wild night of their own.

episodes.name: You're Fired!
episodes.overview: Beast Boy's behavior causes him to be fired from the Teen Titans and replaced by a pair of shape-shifting twins.

episodes.name: Super Robin
episodes.overview: Envious of the other Titans' superpowers following their fight with the H.I.V.E. Five (consisting of Mammoth, Gizmo, Jinx, Billy Numerous, and See-More), Robin wants some of his own. After a disastrous scientific experiment goes awry that merges him with the DNA of the American Robin, he convinces Raven to use her magic to give him superpowers even though she claims that superpowers are a curse.

episodes.name: Tower Power
episodes.overview: Cyborg plugs into the control panel of the Titans tower and drives the others crazy.

episodes.name: Parasite
episodes.overview: Starfire's new pet is a horribly dangerous parasite, but Robin is the only one who is suspicious of the beast.

episodes.name: Starliar
episodes.overview: Beast Boy teaches Starfire how to lie and it backfires as her lies get more and more outrageous.

episodes.name: Meatball Party
episodes.overview: Raven eats a bad meatball that causes tentacles to spring from her teeth and devour the other Titans.

episodes.name: Staff Meeting
episodes.overview: When Robin's long bo-staff is accidentally broken by the other four Titans, he seeks a new one at the mystical Tree of the Universe.

episodes.name: Terra-ized
episodes.overview: When Beast Boy believes that Terra is his new beloved sweetheart and girlfriend, Raven is suspicious of her true motives.

episodes.name: Artful Dodgers
episodes.overview: The Titans believe they will win an upcoming dodgeball championship.

episodes.name: Burger vs. Burrito
episodes.overview: Cyborg and Beast Boy are in perfect sync, except when it comes to their taste in food. What’s the best food ever created, burgers or burritos? The two friends have an all-out competition to settle things once and for all.

episodes.name: Matched
episodes.overview: Cyborg’s Love Matcher 5000 program pairs Raven with Beast Boy and Starfire with Aquaman. While Beast Boy does everything he can to get Raven to love him, Robin tries to be more like Aquaman to win Starfire’s heart.

episodes.name: Colors of Raven
episodes.overview: A magical prism causes Raven to fragment into five distinct personalities which wreak havoc around town until the other Titans can figure out how to rejoin her.

episodes.name: The Left Leg
episodes.overview: When the gang bands together to form a giant robot, Robin is relegated to the left leg, but he makes the left leg count!

episodes.name: Books
episodes.overview: The Titans discover the wonders of reading, but after opening a book that brings their thoughts to life, they must fight against their own imaginations!

episodes.name: Lazy Sunday
episodes.overview: Cyborg and Beast Boy love lazy Sundays sitting on the couch … even when it’s a Tuesday! But when Robin replaces the couch with a treadmill, the two lazy teens must embrace the new active lifestyle.

episodes.name: Starfire the Terrible
episodes.overview: When Robin needs an archenemy, Starfire generously offers to fill the role and she exceeds expectations.

episodes.name: Power Moves
episodes.overview: When Robin starts doing power moves with Cyborg, Beast Boy gets very jealous.

episodes.name: Staring at the Future
episodes.overview: Cyborg and Beast Boy have a staring contest that lasts 30 years, bringing them face to face with a future of adulthood and responsibility… and they hate it.

episodes.name: No Power
episodes.overview: Feeling the other Titans depend too much on their super powers, Robin challenges them to go 24 hours without using their powers. To his distress, they all succeed, leading him to question his own value to the team.

episodes.name: Sidekick
episodes.overview: Robin gets called back to the Batcave but only as a house-sitter while Batman’s away.

episodes.name: Caged Tiger
episodes.overview: Cyborg, Beast Boy, and Robin return from a Bro-cation closer than ever, but their bro-mentum is interrupted by Dr. Light!

episodes.name: Second Christmas
episodes.overview: The Titans trick Starfire into believing in second Christmas with a second Santa.

episodes.name: Nose Mouth
episodes.overview: Raven's past powers may cause consequences to the other Titans.

episodes.name: Legs
episodes.overview: After Robin swipes her cloak, Raven's leggy figure is revealed and she transforms into Lady Legasus. Meanwhile, Cyborg gets stuck in the discarded cloak, revealing a dark side of his personality.

episodes.name: Breakfast Cheese
episodes.overview: Starfire convinces the reluctant Titans to try defeating their enemies with compassion rather than violence.

episodes.name: Waffles
episodes.overview: Cyborg and Beast Boy show their love of waffles by making it the only word they say, much to the annoyance of the other Titans.

episodes.name: Be Mine
episodes.overview: It's Valentine's Day, and the Titans are throwing a dance. Beast Boy knows who he wants to go with, and thing is... he wants to go with Terra, his ex-girlfriend, who already made a crack at eliminating the Titans.

episodes.name: Opposites
episodes.overview: Cyborg has a crush on Jinx.

episodes.name: Birds
episodes.overview: Robin removes two mockingbirds from the chimney with a gas he created in his lab. But the chemical mutates the birds into muscular bullies who then move into the tower.

episodes.name: Brain Food
episodes.overview: Beast Boy is tired of being the least intelligent of the Titans. When all of his efforts to get smart fail, he uses Raven's spell book to cast a spell - not to make him smarter, but to make all of the other Titans dumber.

episodes.name: In and Out
episodes.overview: Robin infiltrates the H.I.V.E. Tower to destroy it, but instead he is distracted by its awesomeness!

episodes.name: Little Buddies
episodes.overview: Cyborg wants Pain Bot to be his "little buddy" but is the destructive robot too dangerous to be a sidekick?

episodes.name: Missing
episodes.overview: Killer Moth offers a reward for Silkie's return, but will Silkie be happier away from the Titans?

episodes.name: Uncle Jokes
episodes.overview: Starfire is allowed to join Beast Boy and Cyborg's revelry, if she avoids uncle jokes.

episodes.name: Mas Y Menos
episodes.overview: Robin tries to teach Spanish-speaking brothers his superhero ways.

episodes.name: Dreams
episodes.overview: The dream worlds of the Titans.

episodes.name: Grandma Voice
episodes.overview: Cyborg is possessed by a "Grandma Voice", which irritates the Titans.

episodes.name: Real Magic
episodes.overview: Robin dabbles with magic, ignoring Raven's warning that he will anger the magic god.

episodes.name: Puppets, Whaaaaat?
episodes.overview: Robin makes a deal with a sock puppet which turns him and the other titans into puppets.

episodes.name: Mr. Butt
episodes.overview: Blackfire pays a surprise visit to her sister Starfire, saying she wants to spend some quality time with her. The other Titans think that Blackfire is playing another trick, but Starfire is sure that this time Blackfire is serious about reviving their sisterly love

episodes.name: Man Person
episodes.overview: Despite the Titans' protests, Beast Boy becomes convinced that replacing his body parts with robotic limbs makes him more manly.

episodes.name: Pirates
episodes.overview: Aqualad asks Raven out on a date, which makes Beast Boy jealous. Cyborg tries to prove that Aqualad is really a pirate.

episodes.name: Money Grandma
episodes.overview: When Robin starts a smear campaign against all of the other Titans so that he can be re-elected  Team Leader, Raven uses a time machine to bring a great leader from the past to teach Robin how to lead.

episodes.name: I See You
episodes.overview: Robin brings Starfire on a fake stakeout in an attempt to get a kiss, while Cyborg and Beast Boy hold their own stakeout to discover Raven's dark secret.

episodes.name: Brian
episodes.overview: When the Brain captures the Titans to fuel Project B.R.I.A.N., the Titans' little buddies are the only heroes who can save them.

episodes.name: Nature
episodes.overview: When Beast Boy loses his ability to change into animals, he realizes that he’s lost touch with his wild side. He goes to the forest to reconnect with his inner beast, but Mother Nature isn't as great as he had hoped.

episodes.name: Salty Codgers
episodes.overview: Raven is delighted when the other Titans are magically turned into old people during a battle.

episodes.name: Knowledge
episodes.overview: Starfire wants to learn more, but will knowledge make her a bummer?

episodes.name: Slumber Party
episodes.overview: When the other Titans find out that Cyborg is afraid of the dark, they have a slumber party to help him face his fears.

episodes.name: Love Monsters
episodes.overview: Raven warns the Titans not to go near a box containing the Twin Destroyers of Azarath. Starfire can't help it and opens the box, giving hugs and snuggles to the tiny and adorable destroyers... but love only makes the destroyers stronger. Now, the Titans must find a way to get the monsters back in the box before Raven finds out that they were released.

episodes.name: Baby Hands
episodes.overview: Robin has been hiding something under his gloves.

episodes.name: Caramel Apples
episodes.overview: Raven and Starfire clash after Starfire creates a bond with Raven's father, while Robin, Cyborg, and Beast Boy struggle to return to Earth's surface after falling into a deep cavern.

episodes.name: Sandwich Thief
episodes.overview: Robin's perfect sandwich is missing and he will stop at nothing to find it.

episodes.overview: When Control Freak imprisons the Titans in a Pretty Pretty Pegasus world, the Titans decide to use violence to escape, while Raven decides to use friendship and happiness.

episodes.name: Vegetables
episodes.overview: When the team tries to live a vegetarian lifestyle, they learn that living that way is not for everyone.

episodes.name: The Mask
episodes.overview: Robin's mask hides both his secret identity and a horrible secret.

episodes.name: Serious Business
episodes.overview: When Robin rations bathroom time to five minutes per visit, the other Titans try to show him the magic of the bathroom.

episodes.name: Halloween
episodes.overview: Raven tries to get the other titans to enjoy Halloween again.

episodes.name: Boys vs Girls
episodes.overview: The Titans compete against each other to prove who is the better gender.

episodes.name: Body Adventure
episodes.overview: Cyborg is infected with a cold and the Titans shrink down to fight it off.

episodes.name: Road Trip
episodes.overview: Cyborg completely rebuilt the T-Car and takes it out on a road trip.

episodes.name: Thanksgiving
episodes.overview: When Raven’s father Trigon shows up for Thanksgiving dinner, Robin’s seating plan isn't the only thing that gets ruined.

episodes.name: The Best Robin
episodes.overview: Due to the Titans' laziness, Robin creates another team of himself to battle Brother Blood.

episodes.name: Mouth Hole
episodes.overview: Robin wants to gain the power of whistling.

episodes.name: Hot Garbage
episodes.overview: The Titans try to convince Beast Boy to clean his room, but they learn that there is more to garbage than just trash.

episodes.overview: When Nibor, Bizzaro World's Robin, arrives in Jump City, the team decides that they should watch him.

episodes.name: Crazy Day
episodes.overview: When Crazy Day arrives, Raven tries to avoid being driven crazy by her fellow teammates.

episodes.name: Smile Bones
episodes.overview: When Cyborg and Beast Boy teach the others to wolf down their food, the group must battle their own obesity.

episodes.name: Real Boy Adventures
episodes.overview: After transforming himself into 'Fleshy Guy', Cyborg discovers the delight and agony of being human.

episodes.name: Hose Water
episodes.overview: The discovery of a baby bird fuels Starfire and Cyborg to discover their inner children have been awakened.

episodes.name: Let's Get Serious
episodes.overview: Robin attempts to make the Teen Titans to be taken more seriously by the real heroes from Young Justice.

episodes.name: Tamaranian Vacation
episodes.overview: The Titans visit Starfire's home world of Tamaran to try and learn what makes her so sweet and loving.

episodes.name: Rocks and Water
episodes.overview: Raven and Beast Boy are surprised to discover that their exes, Terra and Aqualad, are dating each other.

episodes.name: Multiple Trick Pony
episodes.overview: Robin insists that he is a 'multiple trick pony.'

episodes.name: Truth, Justice and What?
episodes.overview: Pizza is the source of the Titans' goofy humor.

episodes.name: Two Bumble Bees and a Wasp
episodes.overview: When Robin tries to teach the others to have more respect for money, he ends up learning a lesson.

episodes.name: Oil Drums
episodes.overview: Cyborg is looking forward to a marathon of '80s television shows, but the remote appears to be missing.

episodes.overview: The Titans immerse themselves into a variety of video game worlds.

episodes.name: Cool School
episodes.overview: Raven decides to hang out with Rose Wilson because she is cool; the others believe they are lame by comparison so they attend Cool School.

episodes.name: Kicking a Ball and Pretending to Be Hurt
episodes.overview: The Titans learn about the magic of soccer.

episodes.name: Head Fruit
episodes.overview: When Beast Boy's head starts to rattle, Robin suggests that he should find a hobby so that his brain will stop shrinking.

episodes.name: Yearbook Madness
episodes.overview: Beast Boy and Cyborg decide to create a yearbook for the Titans.

episodes.name: Beast Man
episodes.overview: Beast Boy discovers he can transform into an adult man.

episodes.overview: Gizmo convinces the Titans he's kidnapped Cyborg, when in reality Cyborg's just hanging out in the HIVE tower with his girl Jinx. When Gizmo gets annoyed by Cyborg's constant presence, the two start a prank war.

episodes.name: Nean
episodes.overview: Raven is cursed to be nice; meanwhile, Starfire is about to marry a pot of chili.

episodes.name: Campfire Stories
episodes.overview: The Titans are having a terrible time on their camping trip, so Robin suggests that they each tell a scary campfire story.

episodes.name: And the Award for Sound Design Goes to Rob
episodes.overview: Raven just wants some piece and quiet for once, and accidentally makes a magical deal that eliminates all sounds.

episodes.name: The HIVE Five
episodes.overview: The HIVE decides to take the day off so that they can avoid engaging with the Titans, if it is possible.

episodes.name: The Return of Slade
episodes.overview: Beast Boy and Cyborg insist on hiring a clown for a Titans party, even though Robin tells them that clowns are for little kids. When the clown fails to live up to their memories, Cyborg and Beast Boy decide to give the clown some cool updates.

episodes.name: More of the Same
episodes.overview: Can the Titans master the four New Year's traditions in order to break the cycle of bad years?

episodes.name: Some of Their Parts
episodes.overview: Robin uses the prism to split the Titans into five parts so he can pick out the best ones for the team.

episodes.name: Cat's Fancy
episodes.overview: Robin is determined to become a cat in order to get Starfire's attention.

episodes.name: Leg Day
episodes.overview: After a humiliating defeat, Raven and the Titans work on building their lower body strength, becoming the "League of Legs."

episodes.name: Dignity of Teeth
episodes.overview: After Beast Boy gets money from the Tooth Fairy, the other Titans try to get in on the action by knocking out their own teeth.

episodes.name: Croissant
episodes.overview: After learning looks don't matter, Beast Boy undergoes a metamorphosis through a cocoon, becoming an ugly, gross creature.

episodes.name: Spice Game
episodes.overview: Having grown sick of Robin's bland cooking, the other Titans make attempts to spice things up.

episodes.name: I'm the Sauce
episodes.overview: Stuck inside on a rainy day, the Titans do rainy-day activities to keep from boredom.

episodes.name: Hey You, Don't Forget About Me In Your Memory
episodes.overview: When Robin decides to become an all-American class president-type person, he convinces the Titans to return to school with him.

episodes.name: Accept The Next Proposition You Hear
episodes.overview: Robin refuses to give the Titans any more orders so that they'll learn to think for themselves.

episodes.name: The Fourth Wall
episodes.overview: Control Freak informs the Titans that they are on a TV show he created and demands they earn him an award.
Cyborg's real strength comes not from his robot parts, but from his favorite song.

episodes.overview: Robin tries to teach the Titans valuable life lessons by reading them fairytales, but the others co-opt his stories and spin them into their own twisted yarns.

episodes.name: A Farce

episodes.name: Scary Figure Dance

episodes.overview: It's Beast Boy's birthday, but no one will celebrate it.

episodes.name: Black Friday
episodes.overview: After refusing to shop on Black Friday, Starfire is visited by the ghosts of Black Friday past, present, and future.

episodes.name: Two Parter (2)
episodes.overview: The Titans must save the members of the Justice League from the clutches of the supervillan Darkseid.

episodes.overview: The Titans attempt to infiltrate Santa's workshop to get their names taken off the Naughty List.

episodes.name: Squash & Stretch
episodes.overview: The Titans learn about cartoon-style violence while trying to get back a bowl of nuts from a Sqirrel.

episodes.name: Garage Sale
episodes.overview: Robin makes the other Titans sell their treasured mementos from past episodes.

episodes.overview: Cyborg is building stress up, to the point where he directs his built-up rage onto the other Titans. To help calm him down, Starfire takes Cyborg into her own, little secret garden.

episodes.overview: The Titans go to watch Lebron James at the Wacka Doodles Amusement Park, but find no one is there.

episodes.name: How 'Bout Some Effort
episodes.overview: It's Valentine's Day and Cyborg goes to great lengths to make it special for his girlfriend Jinx.

episodes.overview: Beast Boy makes lots of money due to a pyramid scheme and convinces the other Titans to join in.

episodes.overview: Beast Boy pinches the other Titans on St. Patty's Day, making them pinch him back, resulting in them all getting curse with bad luck.

episodes.overview: The Easter Bunny is missing, and it's up to the Titans to find him before Easter is ruined.

episodes.overview: The Titans try to outprank each other on April Fools' Day.

episodes.name: Bottle Episode
episodes.overview: After they are trapped in a giant bottle in their living room, the Titans reminisce to pass the time.

episodes.overview: Lady Legasus must stop the League of Legs.

episodes.overview: In order to prevent Robin from eavesdropping, the other Titans begin communicating in Pig Latin.

episodes.name: Wally T

episodes.name: Rad Dudes with Bad Tudes
episodes.overview: Robin tries to emulate rollerbladers.

episodes.overview: The Titans must use ninjutsu to get the McGuffin.

Then, after the girls compete with three of the Titans to see who's better, and Mojo Jojo traps Cyborg and Beast Boy in his new lair, the girls defeat him, with "help" from Robin, Starfire, and Raven.

episodes.overview: Still shipwrecked on a desert island, the Titans try to find food but stumble upon dinosaurs instead.

episodes.overview: Robin eavesdrops on the Titans and grant them wishes to teach them life lessons, but things didn't go as he hoped.

episodes.overview: The Titans get sick of the island and decide to leave, only to realize that they have in fact been unknowingly press-ganged into a reality TV show by the Teen Titans villains and Control Freak.

episodes.overview: Having watched everything on TV, the Titans decide to make their own show.

episodes.overview: Black Manta offers to build the Titans a new pool, but Robin thinks the construction process is too slow.

episodes.overview: The Titans time travel back to the 1990s so they can visit a video store but encounter a familiar foe.

episodes.name: TV Knight 7
episodes.overview: To avoid chores, Batman and Gordon time travel to the future, but still find ways to watch TV.

episodes.overview: Since the commercials are the only part of the show he likes, Control Freak creates extra ads to torment the Titans.

episodes.name: Jump City Rock
episodes.overview: The Titans team up with Nandi and Thomas Bushell to take down The Joker.

episodes.name: Natural Gas
episodes.overview: Outraged at the price they pay for water, gas, and electricity, the Titans go off the grid.

episodes.name: 50% Chad
episodes.overview: Having grown tired of their current villains, the Titans hold an audition for a new arch nemesis.

episodes.name: The Score
episodes.overview: The Titans have a hard time dealing with their emotions when an evil composer changes the music in their show.
Wanting their 365th episode to be extra special, the Titans head to the Warner Bros. studio lot to find a director.

episodes.name: Welcome to Halloween
episodes.overview: Continuing their adventure with Pepo, the Titans escape the cold in a nearby castle, where they meet Krampus.

episodes.name: The Great Holiday Escape
episodes.overview: When they learn that Beast Boy sent Santa to jail, the Titans plan to infiltrate the prison to break him out.

episodes.name: Looking for Love
episodes.overview: When they receive an alert that Love is missing, the Titans set out to find her using musical clues.

episodes.name: Teen Titans Action
episodes.overview: The Titans learn that toys from comedy shows don't sell, so they vow to become action heroes. Having grown tired of their new action lifestyle, the Titans try to break their deal with Toy Master, even enlisting help from the Justice League.

episodes.name: TV Knight 8
episodes.overview: Commissioner Gordon has to work, so Batman joins him at the GCPD for fun and crimefighting.

episodes.name: A Stickier Situation
episodes.overview: When Sticky Joe tries to clip his pet rat's nails, it leads to a wild adventure.

episodes.name: Winning a Golf Tournament Is the Solution to All of Life's Money Problems
episodes.overview: After the T-Car is towed due to outstanding parking tickets, Robin has Cyborg enter a golf tournament for the cash prize.

episodes.name: Always Be Crimefighting
episodes.overview: Looking to motivate them, Robin tells the Titans to solve some crimes or they're fired.

episodes.name: Easter Annihilation
episodes.overview: When Cyborg's egg hunt tech stops working, the Titans go to their satellite to find out what happened.

episodes.name: The Brain of the Family
episodes.overview: The Brain's home life is disrupted when his slacker brother Brian comes to visit. Now The Brain and Mallah have to deal with Brian's messes and keep him from ruining their big secret scheme.

episodes.name: Arthur
episodes.overview: Robin threatens to fire Dr. Light unless he starts coming up with more inventive schemes.

episodes.name: Toilet Water
episodes.overview: When the Titans dog-sit for Superman, Robin tries to keep the others from spoiling Krypto.

episodes.name: Plot Holes
episodes.overview: After learning about movie plot holes, the Titans have some fun but end up throwing their world into chaos.

episodes.name: Utility Belt
episodes.overview: Worried that he's only special because of his utility belt, Robin donates it to a thrift store.

episodes.overview: On a camping trip, The Chief shows off his beard, but warns the Doom Patrol about the Beard Hunter.

episodes.name: Elasti-Bot
episodes.overview: After ElastGirl is pushed to her limit, The Chief builds a robot replacement.

episodes.name: Negative Feels
episodes.overview: Negative Girls starts feeding on negative energy, so the Doom Patrol must stay positive before it's too late.

episodes.name: New Chum
episodes.overview: To prove he is extreme, Robotman becomes friends with King Shark and his gang of suckerfish.

episodes.name: Haunted Tank
episodes.overview: At a Halloween festival, the Titans meet the famous Haunted Tank and its ghostly inhabitant, General Tucker.

episodes.overview: The Titans are in charge of the 100th anniversary party for Warner Bros on the studio lot, and everything is going well until the magical WB Shield is broken into pieces.

episodes.overview: The Titans make wishes on a wishbone, but when it's broken, they must travel to Gobble-Gobble Land to set things right.

episodes.name: Christmas Magic
episodes.overview: After the Titans get shrunken by Mumbo's magic, they must scale a Christmas Tree to prevent Mumbo from ruining their Christmas.

episodes.overview: Starfire is the captain of a spaceship heading back to her home planet of Tarmaran and her crew is some of Earth's finest specimens.

episodes.name: Catpin Freak

episodes.name: 50% Crew

episodes.name: Five Bucks
episodes.overview: Starfire and her crew play Tooth Fairy for the Tooth Fairy.

episodes.name: Wild Card
episodes.overview: Starfire and her crew go on a dangerous mission to prevent Blackfire from acquiring a powerful Tamaranean relic.

episodes.name: Azarath, Metrion Bookstore

episodes.name: The Great Azarathian Face Off
episodes.overview: When a visiting author notices the magical abilities of the bookstore gang, she invites them to be contestants on a new game show on TV.

episodes.name: Bookyman
episodes.overview: When Trigon claims to not be afraid of anything, Nana reminds him of a childhood fear.

episodes.name: Unleashed
episodes.overview: Trigon shows off his collection of conquered planets, which includes Acmetropolis.

episodes.name: Original Idea
episodes.overview: After Trigon proclaims the entire bookstore is his domain, Nana informs him that he has no control in the public domain.

episodes.name: Attention to Detail
episodes.overview: The Titans retreat to an underground bunker after a distress signal, where they enjoy footage from their past adventures, only to notice something isn't right.

episodes.name: The Ranch
episodes.overview: The Titans must accompany their animation team to the new offices.

episodes.name: TV Knight 9
episodes.overview: Batman and Commissioner Gordon are ready for another evening in front of the TV, but Alfred is determined to watch his show.
